Package: CalibrationCurves
Type: Package
Title: Calibration Performance
Version: 4.0.0
Authors@R: c(person(given = "Bavo", family = "De Cock", role = c("aut", "cre"),
     email = "bavo.decock@kuleuven.be"),
    person(given = "Lasai", family = "Barrenada", role = "aut"),
      person(given = "Daan", family = "Nieboer", role = "aut"),
      person(given = "Ben", family = "Van Calster", role = "aut"),
      person(given = "Ewout", family = "Steyerberg", role = "aut"),
      person(given = "Yvonne", family = "Vergouwe", role = "aut"))
Description: Plots calibration curves and computes statistics for assessing
    calibration performance of binary, survival, competing-risks, ordinal and
    multinomial prediction models. Includes tools for modern recalibration
    (Platt scaling, isotonic regression) and a unified calibrate() interface.
    See Barrenada et al. (2025) <doi:10.1017/rsm.2025.10046>, De Cock Campo
    (2023) <doi:10.48550/arXiv.2309.08559> and Van Calster et al. (2016)
    <doi:10.1016/j.jclinepi.2015.12.005>.
License: GPL (>= 3)
